parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night.
The failure of the electrical system can cause a loss of critical vehicle functions, increasing the risk of accidents and stranding the driver.
symptoms: power door locks and window locks inoperative

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to lose critical information, increasing the risk of accidents and stranding the driver.
The failure of the airbag and safety system can cause the airbags to fail to deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: airbags fail to deploy in an accident
OnStar system fails to notify authorities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shifter cable assembly can cause the vehicle to shift into an unintended gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or strandings.
symptoms: The shifter indicator shows an incorrect gear
the shifter is stuck in park
the shifter is difficult to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer control module can cause the speedometer to malfunction, leading to inaccurate speed readings, which can cause accidents, especially on snowy or slippery roads.
symptoms: the speedometer doesn't work at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transfer Case and Four-Wheel Drive System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case and four-wheel drive system can cause loss of traction, loss of control, and accidents, especially on snowy or slippery roads.
symptoms: The four-wheel drive system doesn't engage
the front wheels make a grinding noise
the vehicle sways from side to side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause loss of control, accidents, or strandings.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the transmission revs high during shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: headlights remain off for several minutes
headlights return to normal after a short time
headlights malfunction regardless of road conditions.
